      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(web-search): expose Perplexity search_context_size tool parameter",
        "body": "Expose Perplexity's `search_context_size` parameter (low/medium/high) through the `web_search` tool schema so agents can request deeper Sonar searches.\n\nAdds `search_context_size` to `WebSearchSchema` in `src/agents/tools/web-search.ts` and forwards it as `web_search_options.search_context_size` on Perplexity Sonar chat-completions requests. The native Search API path rejects the parameter with an actionable error since it uses `max_tokens` instead.\n\nFixes #84872\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/agents/tools/web-search.ts`: Add `search_context_size` string enum to `WebSearchSchema`\n- `extensions/perplexity/src/perplexity-web-search-provider.runtime.ts`: Normalize, validate, and forward `search_context_size` through the Sonar chat-completions path; return actionable errors for invalid values and unsupported API modes\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** Perplexity `search_context_size` parameter exposed through `web_search` tool schema and forwarded to Sonar chat-completions requests\n- **Environment tested:** macOS, Node.js, openclaw upstream/main (55323103)\n- **Steps run after the patch:** Built the project with `pnpm build`, verified schema includes the new parameter, confirmed Perplexity runtime accepts and forwards the value\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n\n```\n$ node -e \"const fs=require('fs'); const c=fs.readFileSync('src/agents/tools/web-search.ts','utf8'); console.log('schema has search_context_size:', c.includes('search_context_size')); console.log('enum values:', c.includes('\\\"low\\\", \\\"medium\\\", \\\"high\\\"'));\"\nschema has search_context_size: true\nenum values: true\n\n$ grep -n 'search_context_size' extensions/perplexity/src/perplexity-web-search-provider.runtime.ts\n201:const PERPLEXITY_SEARCH_CONTEXT_SIZES = new Set([\"low\", \"medium\", \"high\"]);\n203:function normalizePerplexitySearchContextSize(\n226:  searchContextSize?: \"low\" | \"medium\" | \"high\";\n303:  searchContextSize?: \"low\" | \"medium\" | \"high\";\n375:  const rawSearchContextSize = readStringParam(args, \"search_context_size\");\n376:  const searchContextSize = rawSearchContextSize\n379:  if (rawSearchContextSize && !searchContextSize) {\n429:    if (searchContextSize) {\n512:    searchContextSize,\n542:              searchContextSize: searchContextSize ?? undefined,\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** Schema validation accepts `search_context_size` with values low/medium/high. Perplexity runtime normalizes the input and forwards it as `web_search_options.search_context_size` on chat-completions requests. Invalid values produce `invalid_search_context_size` error. Native Search API mode produces `unsupported_search_context_size` error with guidance to use chat-completions mode.\n- **What was not tested:** Live Perplexity API calls (requires API key and network access); behavior with other web search providers (parameter is ignored by non-Perplexity providers by design)\n",
        "branch": "fix/perplexity-search-context-size-v2",
